<def f='linux-5.3.1/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_hotplug.c' l='624' ll='635' type='void intel_hpd_poll_init(struct drm_i915_private * dev_priv)'/>
<doc f='linux-5.3.1/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/display/intel_hotplug.c' l='608'>/**
 * intel_hpd_poll_init - enables/disables polling for connectors with hpd
 * @dev_priv: i915 device instance
 *
 * This function enables polling for all connectors, regardless of whether or
 * not they support hotplug detection. Under certain conditions HPD may not be
 * functional. On most Intel GPUs, this happens when we enter runtime suspend.
 * On Valleyview and Cherryview systems, this also happens when we shut off all
 * of the powerwells.
 *
 * Since this function can get called in contexts where we&apos;re already holding
 * dev-&gt;mode_config.mutex, we do the actual hotplug enabling in a seperate
 * worker.
 *
 * Also see: intel_hpd_init(), which restores hpd handling.
 */</doc>
<use f='linux-5.3.1/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_drv.c' l='2995' u='c' c='intel_runtime_suspend'/>
